{"actor":"Marc GRIS","comment":null,"created_at":"2026-03-06T12:05:56Z","event_type":"status_changed","id":204,"issue_id":"claudes-steward-0kr","new_value":"{\"status\":\"in_progress\"}","old_value":"{\"id\":\"claudes-steward-0kr\",\"title\":\"Tmux pane capture: periodic transition log for training dataset\",\"description\":\"Capture tail-50 of every tmux pane every 30s, dedup via content hash, write only on state transitions. Output: per-pane JSONL files under ~/.local/share/claude-steward/tmux-captures/{session}/{window}.{pane}.jsonl. Each record is a self-contained training sample (timestamp, hash, text). No classification at capture time — raw unlabeled data. Classification happens downstream: either manual labeling + trained classifier, or direct LLM inference.\",\"status\":\"open\",\"priority\":1,\"issue_type\":\"feature\",\"owner\":\"62659262+m-gris@users.noreply.github.com\",\"created_at\":\"2026-03-06T04:05:51Z\",\"created_by\":\"Marc GRIS\",\"updated_at\":\"2026-03-06T04:05:51Z\"}"}
